## What Changed

Realizer v1 proved readiness auditing and remediation dispatch. Realizer v2 extends this with hypothesis-first ideation and direct spoke work dispatch — the missing "idea → implementation" loop.

## Architecture

**Flow:** Hypothesis record created in Minder → grounded against spoke readiness → Gemini-assisted phased plan → user approves phase → PEV-complete task lug written to spoke's `WAI-Spoke/seed/ingest/incoming/`

**Hypothesis record** (Realizer-owned object, no forced integration):
- Fields: id, title, value_path, intended_behavior_change, candidate_spokes[], urgency, opportunity_type, current_confidence, status, grounding_snapshot_id, plan_id
- Status flow: `draft → grounded → planned → ready_for_execution → dispatched`
- Store: `WAI-Spoke/realizer/hypotheses/`

**3 decision classes** (dispatch gating):
- `remediation`: auto-confirm (reversible, already implicitly authorized)
- `feature`: user-reviews
- `destructive`: always user

**Dispatch**: `POST /api/realizer/hypothesis/<id>/dispatch/<phase_num>` → writes task lug to `{spoke_path}/WAI-Spoke/seed/ingest/incoming/` (creates dir if needed)

## Build Waves

| Wave | Tasks | Parallel | Unblocked by |
|------|-------|----------|--------------|
| A | task-minder-realizer-inline-foundation-repair-v1 | — | ready now |
| B | hypothesis-schema, hypothesis-ui, spoke-mapping | yes | Wave A |
| C | hypothesis-grounding, draft-plan-gen | yes | Wave B |
| D | decision-classes, hypothesis-dispatch | sequential | Wave C |

## Deferred (check-later cautions)

- Measurement profiles — explicitly deferred until hypothesis loop proves value
- Gardener/Tender/Expediter reconciliation — cleaner separation now
- Adoption/value-review lug types (Phase 4)
- Cross-spoke awareness (Phase 5)
- Approval learning (Phase 6)

